  "text": "The study team is recruiting up to 60 (n ¼ 20/group) sedentary older men and women !65 years of age with objective signs of functional limitations. Inclusion criteria include a long-distance (400 m) corridor walk test time of >290 s indicating functional limitations and moderate to low aerobic fitness, [CITATION_1] , and a sedentary lifestyle defined as <150 min/wk of moderate physical activity as assessed by the Community Healthy Activities Model Program for Seniors (CHAMPS) questionnaire [CITATION_2] .",
